1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,128
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,211 --> 00:00:06,381
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,383 --> 00:00:09,300
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

4
00:00:09,384 --> 00:00:10,760
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

5
00:00:10,844 --> 00:00:12,846
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

6
00:00:12,929 --> 00:00:16,808
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

7
00:00:16,891 --> 00:00:20,103
[Atoy] <i>What do I need to hit</i>
<i>to win the biggest teddy bear?</i>

8
00:00:20,186 --> 00:00:22,272
[attendant] <i>The three in a row, sir.</i>

9
00:00:23,106 --> 00:00:24,315
[both] Hey!

10
00:00:24,399 --> 00:00:25,775
[Ibyang] You're amazing, Master!

11
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:27,277
[attendant] Congrats, sir.

12
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:28,611
I'll buy you something
more expensive than that.

13
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:31,322
[Tonet] <i>Are you stalking me</i>
<i>and Atoy? Or just Atoy?</i>

14
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:32,907
[Audrey scoffs, in English] <i>Of course not.</i>

15
00:00:32,991 --> 00:00:35,410
I have no interest in your boyfriend.

16
00:00:35,493 --> 00:00:36,911
[Tonet] <i>It's good that we're</i>
<i>clear on that.</i>

17
00:00:36,995 --> 00:00:39,205
[Audrey] <i>Show off.</i>

18
00:00:39,289 --> 00:00:43,835
We will hold the annual beauty pageant
for the primary level.

19
00:00:43,918 --> 00:00:45,712
Don't you dare join the pageant,

20
00:00:45,795 --> 00:00:47,172
because you'll only embarrass yourself.

21
00:00:47,255 --> 00:00:48,965
I'll beat you!

22
00:00:49,048 --> 00:00:50,383
[Atoy] <i>I'll take care of Ibyang's gown.</i>

23
00:00:50,467 --> 00:00:53,052
That's what our machines
and fabrics are for.

24
00:00:53,136 --> 00:00:54,554
[in English] Contestant number 1!

25
00:00:54,637 --> 00:00:57,432
[Dmitri, in English] <i>I really hope</i>
<i>you find forgiveness in your heart.</i>

26
00:00:57,515 --> 00:00:59,601
I want to make it up to you
and your daughter.

27
00:00:59,684 --> 00:01:01,061
[in English] Just give me some time.

28
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:03,521
[Cita] <i>Do you want to reconcile with her?</i>

29
00:01:03,605 --> 00:01:06,066
What for? She already has a child.

30
00:01:06,149 --> 00:01:08,777
That's why "Audrey" broke up with you,

31
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:10,320
because you're too grumpy.

32
00:01:10,403 --> 00:01:12,405
[Tonet, in Visayan]
<i>Let's make your ex jealous.</i>

33
00:01:12,489 --> 00:01:13,490
I said you smell nice.

34
00:01:13,573 --> 00:01:15,283
Hmm, so good.

35
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:18,244
[Audrey] <i>Where is Ibyang's mother?</i>

36
00:01:18,328 --> 00:01:19,829
[Tonet] <i>We're still looking for her.</i>

37
00:01:19,913 --> 00:01:22,874
But for now, Atoy and I
are acting as her parents.

38
00:01:22,957 --> 00:01:25,043
I have an old VIP client.

39
00:01:25,126 --> 00:01:26,961
Sir, this kid I'm taking care of

40
00:01:27,045 --> 00:01:28,379
has an event at school tomorrow.

41
00:01:28,463 --> 00:01:29,589
[Atoy] <i>I won't be available.</i>

42
00:01:29,672 --> 00:01:32,884
Yes, sir. Same meeting place.

43
00:01:32,967 --> 00:01:34,010
Yes.

44
00:01:34,093 --> 00:01:35,428
PREVIOUSLY

45
00:01:35,512 --> 00:01:37,472
[music fades]

46
00:01:37,555 --> 00:01:38,973
Hello, everyone!

47
00:01:39,057 --> 00:01:44,604
We're here in Barangay Tabang Lupa
to share food with all the children here.

48
00:01:44,687 --> 00:01:47,690
As you can see,
we're helping so many kids,

49
00:01:47,774 --> 00:01:53,655
and I know we couldn't do this without
all your support for my outreach programs.

50
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:57,659
[muffled chattering in the distance]

51
00:01:57,742 --> 00:01:59,869
Cathy, can we talk?

52
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:02,789
[in English] Can't you see
I'm working here?

53
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:05,625
I'm really sorry about the other day.

54
00:02:05,708 --> 00:02:07,627
I know we had a bad time
at the theme park.

55
00:02:08,211 --> 00:02:11,339
- But I didn't mean for that to happen.
- [gentle music playing]

56
00:02:11,422 --> 00:02:15,301
Okay. What else? Do you have more to say?

57
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:18,221
And he really wants to date you.

58
00:02:19,556 --> 00:02:20,723
This weekend, maybe?

59
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:23,101
Karla, what makes you think I'd agree?

60
00:02:23,726 --> 00:02:25,728
I don't like shady characters.

61
00:02:26,312 --> 00:02:29,482
There are rumors
about that family being smugglers.

62
00:02:29,566 --> 00:02:31,276
Gavin isn't like that.

63
00:02:31,359 --> 00:02:32,819
He's decent.

64
00:02:32,902 --> 00:02:35,613
He won't repeat his family's mistakes.

65
00:02:35,697 --> 00:02:38,867
And he wouldn't be friends
with us if he weren't kind.

66
00:02:40,410 --> 00:02:41,995
Just give him a chance.

67
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:44,497
Just one date!

68
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:48,585
And if you really don't like him,
then reject him.

69
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:50,545
[light music playing]

70
00:02:50,628 --> 00:02:52,797
So? Deal?

71
00:02:55,258 --> 00:02:56,634
[music fades]

72
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:58,136
[Janine, in English] <i>Wow, Mommy!</i>

73
00:02:58,219 --> 00:02:59,929
All of these are for me?

74
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:03,391
Yes, child! So you'll have choices.

75
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:06,811
They're all so beautiful, Mommy!

76
00:03:07,478 --> 00:03:09,480
[in English] I'm so happy you're happy.

77
00:03:10,231 --> 00:03:14,235
Pick your top three,
and we'll use those for tomorrow.

78
00:03:15,653 --> 00:03:17,614
Which one is the most expensive gown here?

79
00:03:17,697 --> 00:03:18,823
Um…

80
00:03:19,657 --> 00:03:22,577
[pensive music playing]

81
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:24,746
[Dmitri chuckles] How's my granddaughter?

82
00:03:24,829 --> 00:03:25,914
Dad.

83
00:03:25,997 --> 00:03:28,958
I'm choosing the most expensive gown!

84
00:03:30,251 --> 00:03:32,503
"I'm choosing, Grandpa."

85
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:36,257
I'm choosing a gown, Grandpa.

86
00:03:36,341 --> 00:03:37,634
Oh.

87
00:03:37,717 --> 00:03:42,388
Um, Janine, why don't you…
play outside first?

88
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:44,682
I just need to talk to your mom. Okay?

89
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:46,267
Go on, child.

90
00:03:46,351 --> 00:03:47,393
[in English] I'll see you later.

91
00:03:47,477 --> 00:03:48,519
Yes. [soft chuckle]

92
00:03:55,735 --> 00:04:00,531
Um, Audrey, I was just thinking…

93
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:02,367
[music fades]

94
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:05,328
Maybe you'd want to look
for Janine's father.

95
00:04:05,828 --> 00:04:07,121
What for, Dad?

96
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:10,917
So you can be a complete family.

97
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:12,460
[in English] Who knows?

98
00:04:12,543 --> 00:04:14,629
Maybe you two could still work things out.

99
00:04:14,712 --> 00:04:16,297
[somber music playing]

100
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:21,511
You know that I'm doing this
to make it up to you.

101
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:25,181
[in English] I-I understand, Dad.

102
00:04:26,599 --> 00:04:27,892
[in English] But no, thank you.

103
00:04:28,559 --> 00:04:30,395
No need to look for that man anymore.

104
00:04:30,478 --> 00:04:31,688
[in English] Are you sure?

105
00:04:31,771 --> 00:04:33,022
[Audrey scoffs]

106
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:35,108
[in English] It's been eight years.

107
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:39,946
I'm sure wherever he is, he's happy.

108
00:04:40,655 --> 00:04:42,740
He has his own life now.

109
00:04:42,824 --> 00:04:46,494
[music intensifies]

110
00:04:49,622 --> 00:04:52,125
[suave theme music playing]

111
00:04:53,584 --> 00:04:55,795
[motorcycle revving]

112
00:04:55,878 --> 00:04:57,255
[sewing machine whirring]

113
00:04:59,257 --> 00:05:00,216
[snipping]

114
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,677
[sewing machine clacking]

115
00:05:05,763 --> 00:05:07,473
[gunshots blasting]

116
00:05:08,349 --> 00:05:09,767
[clicking]

117
00:05:10,518 --> 00:05:11,853
[snipping]

118
00:05:12,979 --> 00:05:14,856
[electronic blipping]

119
00:05:19,110 --> 00:05:20,570
[music fades]

120
00:05:20,653 --> 00:05:24,032
Karla! Did you talk to Cathy?

121
00:05:24,115 --> 00:05:25,199
What did she say?

122
00:05:25,283 --> 00:05:28,036
It's all good! She agreed
to go on a date with you.

123
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,203
Really?!

124
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:32,248
Would I joke about something like this?

125
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:34,042
[in English] You're the best, Karla!

126
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,084
[in English] Yes!

127
00:05:35,168 --> 00:05:36,586
- Whoo!
- Of course.

128
00:05:36,669 --> 00:05:38,838
I said I'd make it up to you, right?

129
00:05:38,921 --> 00:05:40,131
[in English] Thank you!

130
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:43,384
[in English] You know,
I want this to be different.

131
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:46,971
I want our date to be unforgettable.

132
00:05:48,681 --> 00:05:52,643
You should take her to the cemetery!

133
00:05:53,561 --> 00:05:55,646
She'll never forget that, right?

134
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:57,065
You're unbelievable!

135
00:05:59,484 --> 00:06:02,737
But you know, I wish it could be here,
at the basketball court.

136
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:04,030
So it's low-key.

137
00:06:04,906 --> 00:06:07,450
[in English] Humble and rooted,
just like her.

138
00:06:08,367 --> 00:06:11,162
Then afterward, I'll teach her
how to shoot.

139
00:06:11,245 --> 00:06:12,080
Right?

140
00:06:12,163 --> 00:06:13,289
What do you think?

141
00:06:13,372 --> 00:06:16,834
["Sa Wala" instrumental music playing]

142
00:06:17,418 --> 00:06:18,753
Up to you.

143
00:06:21,464 --> 00:06:24,509
[in English] Can you help me set up?
Please?

144
00:06:24,592 --> 00:06:25,635
What?!

145
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:27,637
[in English] Set up?

146
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,222
Come on, Karla!

147
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:31,516
Didn't you say you'd help me?

148
00:06:33,684 --> 00:06:35,019
Come on.

149
00:06:35,728 --> 00:06:36,979
Fine, fine.

150
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:38,397
I'll help you.

151
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:40,817
[in English] I appreciate this.

152
00:06:41,692 --> 00:06:43,444
[in English] You're such
a good friend, Karla!

153
00:06:43,528 --> 00:06:50,118
♪ <i>Not that I'm thinking anything bad…</i> ♪

154
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:53,162
Of course.

155
00:06:53,746 --> 00:06:54,914
That's what friends do.

156
00:06:54,997 --> 00:06:56,415
Help each other, right?

157
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,794
Yes, I have so many plans.

158
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:03,714
I'll change all those lights.

159
00:07:03,798 --> 00:07:06,008
And the music has to be romantic too.

160
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:12,432
♪ <i>Should the heart be made to think…</i> ♪

161
00:07:13,349 --> 00:07:16,060
[muffled chattering]

162
00:07:16,853 --> 00:07:19,355
There. Just enough.

163
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:21,399
My daughter is so beautiful.

164
00:07:21,482 --> 00:07:23,317
Of course, I take after you.

165
00:07:24,152 --> 00:07:25,361
[both chuckle]

166
00:07:26,654 --> 00:07:27,989
Um,

167
00:07:28,072 --> 00:07:30,116
your gown is beautiful too.

168
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:32,827
But do you know how much
this one I'm wearing costs?

169
00:07:34,162 --> 00:07:35,705
[in English] Janine, stop that!

170
00:07:35,788 --> 00:07:36,956
[in English] I'm so sorry.

171
00:07:38,082 --> 00:07:41,627
Janine, don't focus too much on the price.

172
00:07:42,170 --> 00:07:44,213
Just focus on your performance

173
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:46,507
and what we practiced at home.

174
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:56,934
[sneaky music playing]

175
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:00,938
[Atoy] Are we good here?

176
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:02,315
- Hmm, perfect.
- Huh?

177
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:04,275
Your ex saw us.

178
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:08,488
There, look.

179
00:08:09,363 --> 00:08:11,407
She's staring.

180
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:14,660
What's that?

181
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:16,996
My outfit is still better.

182
00:08:17,622 --> 00:08:19,081
Janine!

183
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:24,712
Ibyang, I don't want
any quarrels today, okay?

184
00:08:25,671 --> 00:08:27,089
Why me, Master?

185
00:08:28,174 --> 00:08:29,967
What I'm saying is…

186
00:08:30,051 --> 00:08:34,347
maybe Janine will try
to approach you again.

187
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:36,933
Just avoid her, okay?

188
00:08:37,016 --> 00:08:39,060
I don't want any trouble. Hmm?

189
00:08:39,143 --> 00:08:40,561
Yes, Master.

190
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:42,063
[in English] Very good.

191
00:08:42,146 --> 00:08:43,314
[feel-good music playing]

192
00:08:46,651 --> 00:08:48,402
How about me? Just kidding.

193
00:08:49,987 --> 00:08:51,697
Oh, so beautiful.

194
00:08:52,573 --> 00:08:55,076
Wow! Ibyang looks so beautiful!

195
00:08:55,159 --> 00:08:56,285
Yes, Ibyang!

196
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:58,579
I wasn't wrong to sign you up.

197
00:08:58,663 --> 00:09:00,540
- Thank you!
- She's so beautiful, look!

198
00:09:01,624 --> 00:09:03,626
- [teacher] You're so beautiful!
- [Atoy] Thank you.

199
00:09:05,169 --> 00:09:06,295
[Audrey] You're beautiful, child.

200
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:08,381
You're really going to win.

201
00:09:08,464 --> 00:09:11,801
[tense music playing]

202
00:09:11,884 --> 00:09:13,803
[muffled chattering]

203
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:16,514
[upbeat music playing]

204
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:18,224
[audience whooping]

205
00:09:23,896 --> 00:09:26,107
Is Red not coming?

206
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:27,483
[in English] Unfortunately not, Dad.

207
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:29,944
[in English] He has
a bunch of work meetings today.

208
00:09:30,027 --> 00:09:32,321
[lively chattering]

209
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:35,366
[in English] My God. It's so hot here.

210
00:09:35,449 --> 00:09:36,534
[in English] It is.

211
00:09:37,368 --> 00:09:38,661
[Emerson] Ah, Ibyang!

212
00:09:38,744 --> 00:09:41,956
[group chanting] Ibyang! Ibyang!

213
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:45,293
- Ibyang! Ibyang!
- [indistint]

214
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:47,086
- Ibyang! Ibyang!
- [indistinct]

215
00:09:47,169 --> 00:09:52,091
[cheering and lively chattering]

216
00:09:52,174 --> 00:09:53,718
[Karla] You're all good there, huh!

217
00:09:54,218 --> 00:09:56,304
[Ame, in English] Oh,
thank you, thank you!

218
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:58,222
Ibyang's school is really beautiful!

219
00:09:58,306 --> 00:09:59,849
And it's so big!

220
00:09:59,932 --> 00:10:01,142
Go, Ibyang!

221
00:10:01,225 --> 00:10:02,268
[audience cheering]

222
00:10:02,351 --> 00:10:04,437
- Go, Ibyang!
- Ibyang!

223
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:06,772
[cheering]

224
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:08,107
[Karla] Ibyang!

225
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:10,943
Their auditorium here at Ibyang's school
is so nice, isn't it?

226
00:10:11,027 --> 00:10:12,695
It's beautiful.

227
00:10:12,778 --> 00:10:14,405
It's beautiful, and cool too.

228
00:10:14,488 --> 00:10:16,657
[audience chanting] Ibyang! Ibyang!

229
00:10:16,741 --> 00:10:18,534
Ibyang! Ibyang!

230
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:21,162
Dad, maybe it's better
if we look for another seat?

231
00:10:21,245 --> 00:10:22,580
[audience chanting] Ibyang! Ibyang!

232
00:10:23,289 --> 00:10:25,374
- [in English] There's no vacant…
- [grunts]

233
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:27,627
[in English] Good morning,
ladies and gentlemen.

234
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:30,963
It's time to meet the contestants

235
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:35,968
for the 2026 Little Miss Primary School!

236
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:37,136
[audience cheering]

237
00:10:37,219 --> 00:10:39,138
Ibyang!

238
00:10:39,221 --> 00:10:40,514
[audience cheering]

239
00:10:40,598 --> 00:10:44,143
[in English] Let's meet our first
of the six contestants.

240
00:10:44,226 --> 00:10:46,103
In no particular order,

241
00:10:46,187 --> 00:10:52,234
first, from Grade 2, Ms. Janine Ranoy!

242
00:10:52,318 --> 00:10:53,569
[cheering]

243
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:55,154
[in English] Let's go!

244
00:10:55,237 --> 00:10:59,909
[audience applauding]

245
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:02,203
[in English] Hello! Good morning,
ladies and gentlemen.

246
00:11:02,286 --> 00:11:04,038
[in English] My name is Janine Ranoy,

247
00:11:04,121 --> 00:11:09,085
and I am here to show each
and every one of you perfection!

248
00:11:09,168 --> 00:11:11,087
[in English] I thank you!

249
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,005
[in English] All right!

250
00:11:13,089 --> 00:11:15,049
[applauding]

251
00:11:15,132 --> 00:11:17,968
She looks beautiful,
but she is so arrogant, huh?

252
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:20,012
- No holding back.
- Yes, oh.

253
00:11:20,096 --> 00:11:23,391
[in English] Second contestant
comes from Grade 1.

254
00:11:23,474 --> 00:11:27,645
The youngest of all the contestants,

255
00:11:27,728 --> 00:11:30,272
Ivy Santos!

256
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:32,566
- [audience cheering]
- Yes! Ivy!

257
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:34,610
[audience chanting] Ibyang! Ibyang!

258
00:11:34,693 --> 00:11:37,279
If only you moved properly,
you wouldn't have stepped on anyone.

259
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:38,489
[Dmitri, in English] It's okay, Martina.

260
00:11:38,572 --> 00:11:39,532
[in English] Don't mind it.

261
00:11:39,615 --> 00:11:41,492
[chanting] Ibyang! Ibyang! Ibyang!

262
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:44,078
- [whoops, in English] Go, Ibyang!
- [in English] Go, Ibyang!

263
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:46,372
The whole barangay's support

264
00:11:46,455 --> 00:11:48,165
- is overwhelming, Atoy!
- Right?!

265
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:49,875
[audience applauding]

266
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:52,002
- [in English] Yes!
- [in English] Yes! Let's go, Ibyang!

267
00:11:52,086 --> 00:11:53,546
[Tonet shrieks]

268
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:56,132
Good morning!

269
00:11:56,215 --> 00:11:59,009
This is my first time
joining something like this.

270
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:04,014
I'm so excited to experience
everything for the first time!

271
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:05,850
[cheering]

272
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:07,017
[cheering]

273
00:12:07,101 --> 00:12:08,310
[Karla] Ibyang!

274
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:10,729
[audience chanting] Ibyang!

275
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:13,691
Ibyang! Ibyang!

276
00:12:13,774 --> 00:12:14,859
Thank you!

277
00:12:14,942 --> 00:12:17,528
[cheering]

278
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:20,531
Give me my cellphone,
so we can take pictures of her!

279
00:12:20,614 --> 00:12:22,491
- I'll just get it from the dressing room.
- Okay.

280
00:12:23,993 --> 00:12:27,079
Looks like she might win.
That can't happen.

281
00:12:27,163 --> 00:12:32,126
[emcee, in English] Our third contestant,
from Grade 6, Anaiah Ong!

282
00:12:32,209 --> 00:12:34,170
[in English] Hello, everyone!

283
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:40,342
Good morning, and thank you
for this opportunity to join,

284
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:42,720
and thank you to my teachers.

285
00:12:42,803 --> 00:12:46,056
[tense music playing]

286
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:03,991
- [suspicious music playing]
- Uh--

287
00:13:04,074 --> 00:13:05,451
[Tonet] Oh, oh!

288
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:07,703
Excuse me.

289
00:13:08,454 --> 00:13:10,748
That's my lipstick. Why did you touch it?

290
00:13:10,831 --> 00:13:13,792
[music intensifies]

291
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:20,883
[in English] Once again, the contestants
for the Little Miss Primary School 2026!

292
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:28,390
[audience cheering]

293
00:13:30,976 --> 00:13:34,730
- [epic music playing]
- [cheering, whistling, applause]

294
00:13:34,813 --> 00:13:36,524
[audience cheering] Ibyang! Ibyang!

295
00:13:37,983 --> 00:13:40,194
She's bringing home the crown, sis!

296
00:13:40,277 --> 00:13:41,487
Yes, sis!

297
00:13:41,570 --> 00:13:42,863
[Ame] Ibyang!

298
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:46,825
I think I misplaced my lipstick.

299
00:13:46,909 --> 00:13:47,826
[in English] Sorry.

300
00:13:47,910 --> 00:13:49,161
This?

301
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:50,746
This is mine.

302
00:13:50,829 --> 00:13:52,957
Ah, that's mine.

303
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:56,377
I remember the smears on the side.

304
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:58,087
So, are we good now?

305
00:13:58,671 --> 00:14:00,005
Sorry, but no.

306
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:01,674
That's mine. I bought it.

307
00:14:01,757 --> 00:14:03,509
[tense stinging]

308
00:14:03,592 --> 00:14:08,013
[in English] You must be mistaken,
because that's my shade and my brand.

309
00:14:08,097 --> 00:14:10,641
[stammers] Oh, why?

310
00:14:10,724 --> 00:14:12,768
Doesn't this shade suit me?

311
00:14:15,771 --> 00:14:18,023
[music fades]

312
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:21,569
[emcee, in English] Coming up!
Next will be the talent portion

313
00:14:21,652 --> 00:14:23,779
where our candidates get to showcase

314
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:25,531
their skills in singing,

315
00:14:25,614 --> 00:14:28,868
dancing, acting, and even painting.

316
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:33,205
[suspicious music playing]

317
00:14:41,547 --> 00:14:43,299
Huh? [inhales]

318
00:14:43,382 --> 00:14:44,675
You'll change there, okay?

319
00:14:44,758 --> 00:14:46,135
You can--

320
00:14:46,218 --> 00:14:48,762
Where's Tonet anyway? Let's go.

321
00:14:48,846 --> 00:14:50,514
- I can do this, Master.
- You can do it yourself, huh.

322
00:14:50,598 --> 00:14:52,182
- Hmm, I'm a big girl now!
- [Atoy] Okay.

323
00:14:53,142 --> 00:14:54,894
[Ibyang] All right. Oh.

324
00:14:54,977 --> 00:14:57,813
[upbeat music playing]

325
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:00,900
Janine!

326
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:02,484
- [somber music playing]
- [panting]

327
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:04,320
There. Good thing you're here.

328
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:06,488
- Why?
- I need your help.

329
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:10,284
I'll make sure Ibyang loses.

330
00:15:10,367 --> 00:15:11,201
‪[smirks]

331
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:14,496
There, perfect.

332
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:18,042
[tense suspicious music playing]

333
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:24,840
[Janine] Help me, quick.

334
00:16:04,672 --> 00:16:06,715
Sorry, but why are you so insistent?

335
00:16:07,216 --> 00:16:08,842
Didn't you take it from our table?

336
00:16:08,926 --> 00:16:10,469
Why are you pretending it's yours?

337
00:16:11,553 --> 00:16:13,430
[in English] Ah, you know what?
It's… it's fine.

338
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:14,723
Just take it.

339
00:16:15,683 --> 00:16:19,520
You know, why do you look down
on me so much?

340
00:16:19,603 --> 00:16:21,230
[tense music playing]

341
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:23,857
What? I'm already giving it to you,

342
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:25,859
and you still don't want it?

343
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:27,569
[scoffs, in English] Look.

344
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,989
Let's not make a scene here.

345
00:16:30,572 --> 00:16:32,825
You're the one making a scene!

346
00:16:32,908 --> 00:16:34,868
So, you're saying I'm a liar?!

347
00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:37,788
I never said you're a liar!

348
00:16:39,039 --> 00:16:40,833
Looks like your child picked up
some of your attitude.

349
00:16:40,916 --> 00:16:42,251
What did you say?

350
00:16:42,334 --> 00:16:43,877
Why are you dragging Janine into this?

351
00:16:43,961 --> 00:16:45,087
Because it's true!

352
00:16:46,964 --> 00:16:48,048
You both have the same attitude.

353
00:16:48,132 --> 00:16:50,592
- What's your problem, huh?!
- Hey, hey, hey.

354
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:53,762
[music intensifies]

355
00:17:00,310 --> 00:17:01,979
What's going on here?

356
00:17:02,604 --> 00:17:03,856
[Tonet] Well, it's your ex!

357
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:06,734
She came to our table
and tried to take my lipstick.

358
00:17:06,817 --> 00:17:08,360
I already said it's fine, didn't I?

359
00:17:08,444 --> 00:17:09,820
I even gave it to you!

360
00:17:09,903 --> 00:17:12,364
Why do you have to drag
my daughter into this?

361
00:17:12,448 --> 00:17:13,657
Because it's true!

362
00:17:14,658 --> 00:17:16,994
Why are you taking this personally
over a lipstick?!

363
00:17:17,077 --> 00:17:19,163
[in English] You don't know me,
and you don't know my daughter!

364
00:17:19,246 --> 00:17:20,622
[Atoy] Wait, wait.

365
00:17:21,206 --> 00:17:22,207
Hold on.

366
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:24,918
If you both have the same lipstick…

367
00:17:25,961 --> 00:17:27,504
Maybe it was just misplaced?

368
00:17:29,131 --> 00:17:32,217
Ah! So you're saying
she's right and I'm wrong?!

369
00:17:32,301 --> 00:17:34,887
No, what I'm saying is,
did you check your bag?

370
00:17:34,970 --> 00:17:37,097
[sneaky music playing]

371
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:39,058
[disgruntled scoff]

372
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:43,312
[music fades]

373
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:47,649
See? I don't even know
how my lipstick ended up there.

374
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:51,653
With so many girls around,
maybe one of them played with it.

375
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:54,031
Oh, well then, sorry!

376
00:17:54,114 --> 00:17:56,533
[tense music playing]

377
00:17:57,409 --> 00:18:02,039
Fine. I'll accept your apology,
even if it's sarcastic.

378
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:05,334
Talk to your girlfriend!

379
00:18:05,417 --> 00:18:07,127
[music fades]

380
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:10,172
[sneaky music playing]

381
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:11,757
What did she say? Girlfriend?

382
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:12,966
Mm-hmm.

383
00:18:13,050 --> 00:18:15,511
She's known for a while
that we're in a relationship.

384
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:16,845
[chuckles softly]

385
00:18:17,971 --> 00:18:18,972
[music continues]

386
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:20,849
That's… what you told her?

387
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:23,519
No! That's what she assumed!

388
00:18:23,602 --> 00:18:24,770
She saw us at the theme park, right?

389
00:18:24,853 --> 00:18:26,438
Then she said you were my boyfriend.

390
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:29,942
Then at orientation, she thought
we'd been together for a long time.

391
00:18:30,025 --> 00:18:31,401
So, I didn't correct her.

392
00:18:33,028 --> 00:18:34,571
[chuckles]

393
00:18:34,655 --> 00:18:36,406
You're crazy, Tonet.

394
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:38,534
So what? Do you want
to chase after her? Go ahead.

395
00:18:38,617 --> 00:18:40,911
- [Atoy] Why?
- Do you want to tell her she's wrong?

396
00:18:40,994 --> 00:18:43,664
- What for? No…
- [Tonet] Oh? Ah! So, you're still hoping?

397
00:18:43,747 --> 00:18:44,581
- You're still hoping.
- [Atoy] Hoping?

398
00:18:44,665 --> 00:18:46,291
I'm not hoping. Come on, let's go.

399
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:49,461
Then let's just go along with it,
so she knows you've moved on.

400
00:18:53,715 --> 00:18:54,842
[exclaims] This is it, Ibyang!

401
00:18:54,925 --> 00:18:55,968
Do your best, okay?

402
00:18:56,051 --> 00:18:58,053
Just remember, enjoy the moment.

403
00:18:58,137 --> 00:19:00,180
[in Visayan] You're beautiful,
and you're a good dancer!

404
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:02,599
- [in Visayan] Okay? You got this! [gasps]
- Okay.

405
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:04,351
You can do this. Good luck, Ibyang.

406
00:19:04,434 --> 00:19:05,269
Go on, go on.

407
00:19:05,352 --> 00:19:08,564
We'll just be over there, taking pictures
and videos. Come on, come on, come on.

408
00:19:08,647 --> 00:19:10,023
- Thank you, Sister Tonet.
- [Atoy, in English] Good luck!

409
00:19:10,107 --> 00:19:11,024
I'm really excited!

410
00:19:11,108 --> 00:19:11,984
[exclaims]

411
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:13,652
- Let's go, let's go.
- [Ibyang] Okay, okay.

412
00:19:13,735 --> 00:19:14,695
[Ibyang] Master, oh.

413
00:19:14,778 --> 00:19:16,155
All right.

414
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,580
Ibyang…

415
00:19:24,663 --> 00:19:26,290
I think there's dirt on your face.
Here, look.

416
00:19:26,373 --> 00:19:27,207
- Uh, yes.
- [Ibyang] Really?

417
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:29,084
Ah, yes. Yes. Here, wipe it.

418
00:19:29,168 --> 00:19:30,544
- [Ibyang] Okay.
- [Janine] That's embarrassing.

419
00:19:30,627 --> 00:19:32,337
[student] Fix your makeup first.

420
00:19:32,421 --> 00:19:34,298
Here. Do it like this.

421
00:19:34,965 --> 00:19:38,760
[emcee] From Grade 1, Ivy Santos!

422
00:19:38,844 --> 00:19:41,388
- [Ibyang] Okay, they're calling me.
- Oh, that's enough. Good luck.

423
00:19:41,471 --> 00:19:42,848
- [in English] Good luck!
- [Ibyang] Thanks!

424
00:19:42,931 --> 00:19:45,767
[suspicious music playing]

425
00:19:45,851 --> 00:19:46,768
[cackles]

426
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:51,231
She's really going to be humiliated.

427
00:19:54,651 --> 00:19:56,111
[music fades]

428
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:59,198
[applauding]

429
00:19:59,781 --> 00:20:01,283
Wait, I'm taking a picture.

430
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:02,534
Hurry, hurry.

431
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:06,955
[applauding]

432
00:20:07,039 --> 00:20:08,081
[upbeat music playing]

433
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:10,959
[cheering]

434
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:18,217
[audience jeering]

435
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:22,054
[laughs]

436
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:26,850
[audience jeering]

437
00:20:28,518 --> 00:20:30,062
What… What happened to Ibyang?

438
00:20:30,854 --> 00:20:36,151
[audience jeering]

439
00:20:38,237 --> 00:20:39,404
Janine, your plan is something else.

440
00:20:39,488 --> 00:20:40,530
Exactly.

441
00:20:41,406 --> 00:20:46,161
[audience jeering]

442
00:20:52,376 --> 00:20:54,169
[laughs]

443
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:02,469
- What happened?
- [Tonet] Tell her to get off the stage!

444
00:21:02,552 --> 00:21:03,762
I'm going to clean her face.

445
00:21:03,845 --> 00:21:05,055
Wait, hold on.

446
00:21:05,722 --> 00:21:09,977
- [audience 1] Poor Ibyang.
- [audience 2] Oh, no.

447
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:14,314
[pensive music playing]

448
00:21:15,691 --> 00:21:18,193
[in English] Dad, are you seeing this?

449
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:19,778
[in English] What's happened
with her face?

450
00:21:19,861 --> 00:21:21,530
[in English] Uh, I don't know.

451
00:21:21,613 --> 00:21:24,491
Maybe it's part of her performance.

452
00:21:24,574 --> 00:21:26,326
[in English] I-- I don't think so.

453
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:27,452
I mean, maybe…

454
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:29,413
maybe she's allergic
to whatever's on her face or…

455
00:21:29,496 --> 00:21:31,748
[in English] I don't know.
Is she supposed to be a Smurf?

456
00:21:31,832 --> 00:21:33,417
[in English] Maybe. A Smurf!

457
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:35,043
Quiet, quiet!

458
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:37,879
You're laughing at a child?

459
00:21:38,588 --> 00:21:39,923
You're picking on the kid?

460
00:21:40,007 --> 00:21:41,258
[in English] Excuse me?

461
00:21:41,341 --> 00:21:42,801
[in English] I'm not talking to you.

462
00:21:42,884 --> 00:21:45,470
No, but I'm talking to you.

463
00:21:45,554 --> 00:21:47,347
Martina, don't engage.

464
00:21:47,431 --> 00:21:49,141
[in English] We're not here for that.

465
00:21:49,224 --> 00:21:51,685
[pensive music playing]

466
00:21:55,105 --> 00:21:58,191
But we just talked to her earlier.

467
00:21:58,275 --> 00:21:59,484
She didn't look like that.

468
00:21:59,568 --> 00:22:01,069
Wait, I'll find a way.

469
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:05,657
[suspicious music playing]

470
00:22:11,538 --> 00:22:16,043
Miss, uh… can I ask for help?

471
00:22:19,838 --> 00:22:24,426
Ivy, is that really your makeup?

472
00:22:25,677 --> 00:22:27,095
[music fades]

473
00:22:27,179 --> 00:22:28,597
So, Ivy?

474
00:22:29,514 --> 00:22:31,224
You can do it again later.

475
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:35,187
Have your mom
clean off the blue paint first.

476
00:22:35,937 --> 00:22:39,191
[melancholic music playing]

477
00:22:39,274 --> 00:22:41,526
I don't want to dance anymore.

478
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:42,861
[sobs]

479
00:22:42,944 --> 00:22:44,488
I'll just go home.

480
00:22:45,280 --> 00:22:51,578
[electronic blipping]

481
00:22:54,414 --> 00:22:55,916
[tense music playing]

482
00:22:55,999 --> 00:22:57,000
Go and continue the dance!

483
00:22:57,584 --> 00:22:58,919
What happened to your face?

484
00:22:59,002 --> 00:23:00,295
Well, now we're the same.

485
00:23:00,378 --> 00:23:02,047
[Atoy] <i>Let's go. I'll dance with you.</i>

486
00:23:02,130 --> 00:23:03,090
[audience cheering]

487
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:06,593
[Ibyang] We both know you're the one
who put the blue on my face.

488
00:23:06,676 --> 00:23:08,053
Don't accuse me!

489
00:23:08,136 --> 00:23:09,930
- [thumps softly]
- [groans]

490
00:23:10,013 --> 00:23:11,723
What are you doing to Janine?!

491
00:23:11,807 --> 00:23:12,641
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

492
00:23:12,724 --> 00:23:14,476
[principal] We really
had a hard time deciding,

493
00:23:14,559 --> 00:23:17,062
because the children are all so talented.

494
00:23:17,145 --> 00:23:19,856
[in English] And now
for the most prestigious award of all!

495
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:24,486
[in English] Our 2026
Little Miss Primary School…

496
00:23:24,569 --> 00:23:27,030
UP NEXT

497
00:23:30,867 --> 00:23:33,662
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

498
00:23:33,745 --> 00:23:35,497
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
